---
import SAGPLayout from "../../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Works in Progress | SAGP">

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="kicker">Works in Progress</div>
    <h1>Every polished argument begins as a developing idea.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The SAGP Works in Progress Series provides a setting for scholars to
      present research in development and receive thoughtful feedback from a
      community of colleagues.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>What is the Works in Progress Series?</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      The Works in Progress Series reflects one of the Society’s defining
      commitments: scholarship flourishes through conversation, criticism, and
      intellectual generosity.
    </p>

    <p>
      The series is especially valuable for early-career and mid-career scholars,
      who can present work that is still taking shape and receive constructive
      feedback from colleagues, including senior specialists in the field.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      Works in Progress is not simply an event series. It is one of the ways
      SAGP makes mentorship and scholarly community visible.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Why it matters</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Developing ideas</h3>
      <p>
        Scholars can share research before it is fully polished, when feedback
        can still shape the argument.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Constructive feedback</h3>
      <p>
        Discussion focuses on helping the work become stronger through careful,
        generous, and serious engagement.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Scholarly mentorship</h3>
      <p>
        The series creates opportunities for exchange across career stages and
        across institutions.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Current status</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      The SAGP Works in Progress Series has been moved to spring. The deadline
      for submitting abstracts for the next series will be in January 2027.
      More information will follow as plans take shape.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      Future enhancement: add submission instructions, eligibility information,
      format details, and examples of past Works in Progress sessions when
      available.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>
